 Wednesday June 14th Trench : wet veri cold : on observ : a pretti good sniper is opposit us pot at the periscop when it goe up got veri close at time : heavi bombard round Armentier Yres still seem to be go strong : we got a few shell dure the day : Jim Marsland look me up we had a good yarn : I took a " P" of Jim Bert : one of our aero 's brave the element went up Fritz sent some shot at him : F Pool came down for a few minut after " stand down " had a talk : Told me that W Barham other had join up the 18th so I must look them up when I go out . Thursday June 15th Daylight Save trench : we had to put our watch one hour ahead this morn as the "day light save " start today : got a P.C. from J.B.J. : on fatigu 6am ? 10.30 am build up a parapet : an aero ? came up after tea but did not stop up long : a fair few shell of both side kick around : cold showeri day : our gun bog in all day : Friday June 16th trench : clear up dure morn turn out nice day with glorious moonlight night : plenti of mortar " strafe"dur day usual shell " strafe" : wrote after dinner : about 11 pm our gun gave a "demonstr " all round on the left we certain have some gun : It look well with all the gun flash : Saturday June 17th : The day they forgot to proclaim peac on : trench : fine day : gas alarm on the left about 12.30 am but it did not get round our way : our gun shook him
